# <type>(<scope>): <summary>  ← header, max 72 chars
#
# Example:
#   feat(web): add spam folder note to waitlist success
#
# ── Allowed types ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  feat      A new feature
#  fix       A bug fix
#  chore     Maintenance, dependency updates, tooling (no prod change)
#  docs      Documentation only
#  refactor  Code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
#  perf      Performance improvement
#  test      Adding or correcting tests
#  style     Formatting, whitespace — no logic change
#  ci        CI/CD configuration changes
#  build     Build system or external dependency changes
#  revert    Reverts a previous commit
#
# ── Common scopes ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  web       Next.js frontend app
#  api       Backend / API layer
#  shared    Shared utilities, types, constants
#  infra     Infrastructure, deployment, environment config
#
# ── Body (optional) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Blank line required between header and body.
# Explain WHY, not what — the diff shows what.
# Wrap at ~72 columns. Use bullet points for multiple points:
#
#   - first reason
#   - second reason
#
# ── Footer (optional) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# BREAKING CHANGE: <description>
# Closes #<issue>
#
Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
